    \begin {tikzcd}
    Z\ar [dr, "\tau _j"]\ar [d, dashed, "\exists  !"'] \\
    P\ar [r, "\pi _j"'] & X_j\makebox [0pt][l]{.}
    \end {tikzcd}

When J is the ordinal category 2, hence the diagram is of
  shape \bullet \,\bullet , and so the product is of two objects X and Y,
  this property has the following nice form:




